b'' b'' b'_my advocate_' b'' b'i sinned. and straightway, posthaste, satan flew' b'before the presence of the most high god' b'and made a railing accusation there.' b'he said, "this soul, this thing of clay and sod,' b"has sinned. 'tis true that he has named thy name;" b'but i demand his death, for thou hast said,' b"'the soul that sinneth, it shall die.' shall not" b'thy sentence be fulfilled? is justice dead?' b'send now this wretched sinner to his doom!' b'what other thing can righteous ruler do?"' b'thus satan did accuse me day and night;' b'and every word he spoke, o god, was true!' b'' b"then quickly one rose up from god's right hand," b'before whose glory angels veiled their eyes;' b'he spoke, "each jot and tittle of the law' b'must be fulfilled; the guilty sinner dies!' b'but wait suppose his guilt were all transferred' b'to me and that i paid his penalty!' b'behold my hands, my side, my feet! one day' b'i was made sin for him and died that he' b'might be presented, faultless, at thy throne!"' b'and satan flew away. full well he knew' b'that he could not prevail against such love,' b'for every word my dear lord spoke was true!' b'' b'' b'by martha snell nicholson' b'' b'+++++++++++++++++++++++' b'i heard this poem read last night and wanted to share it with other' b"subscribers of this newsgroup. it's such a wonderful blessing to see how" b'secure our salvation is because the lord jesus paid for what he did not owe' b'because we had a debt which we were not capable to pay.' b'' b'thanks and praise be to the savior, the lord jesus christ, who is seated at' b'the right hand of the majesty on high, making intercession for us.' b'++++++++++++++++++++++++' b'' b'liane brown' 